WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:35.640
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

13
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

14
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!
ONE PIECE

15
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind
Rashinban nante juutai no moto

16
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide
Netsu ni ukasare kaji wo toru no sa

17
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals
Hokori kabutteta takara no chizu mo

18
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real
Tashikameta no nara densetsu janai!

19
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

20
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:16.850
Kojin teki na arashi wa dare ka no

21
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

22
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through
BIORHYTHM nokkatte

23
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it
Omoi sugoseba ii!

24
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

25
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

26
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,
POCKET no COIN

27
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?
Soreto YOU WANNA BE MY FRIEND?

28
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!
WE ARE, WE ARE ON THE CRUISE!

29
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

30
00:01:50.010 --> 00:01:51.920
[MARINES muttering]

31
00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:54.090
[ZORO]
You're going to be
King of the Pirates?

32
00:01:54.470 --> 00:01:54.970
Right...

33
00:01:54.970 --> 00:01:57.350
You must be completely
out of your rubbery mind.

34
00:01:57.350 --> 00:01:59.020
Do you have any idea
what that means?

35
00:01:59.020 --> 00:02:02.770
Yeah, when he first told me, it was
shocking, but he's completely serious!

36
00:02:02.770 --> 00:02:04.310
That's how he is, I suppose.

37
00:02:04.310 --> 00:02:06.860
[LUFFY laughing]

38
00:02:07.570 --> 00:02:13.280
The First

39
00:02:08.020 --> 00:02:09.690
[LUFFY]
Here's what I promised you.

40
00:02:09.690 --> 00:02:10.530
There's three.

41
00:02:10.530 --> 00:02:13.280
I couldn't tell which was yours,
so I just took all of 'em.

42
00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:15.240
All of them belong to me.

43
00:02:15.240 --> 00:02:18.120
I use santoryu: The three-sword style.

44
00:02:18.120 --> 00:02:21.410
Just know that if you fight with me now,
you'll be a government-defying villain.

45
00:02:21.410 --> 00:02:22.620
So it's either that...

46
00:02:22.620 --> 00:02:26.000
or you're left out here and killed
by the Marines execution-style.

47
00:02:26.630 --> 00:02:28.630
What are you, the son of the Devil?

48
00:02:28.630 --> 00:02:31.210
It doesn't matter
'cause if I don't choose your side,

49
00:02:31.210 --> 00:02:33.380
I'll just end up dead on these sticks.

50
00:02:33.380 --> 00:02:34.800
So let's do it.

51
00:02:34.800 --> 00:02:36.010
[laughs]

52
00:02:36.010 --> 00:02:38.180
So you're finally gonna join my crew!

53
00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:40.930
This is the best thing ever! [laughs]

54
00:02:40.930 --> 00:02:44.020
Would you quit celebrating already
and get these ropes off me?!

55
00:02:41.560 --> 00:02:42.850
All right!

56
00:02:42.850 --> 00:02:44.020
[LUFFY laughs]

57
00:02:44.020 --> 00:02:44.890
What the...?

58
00:02:44.440 --> 00:02:47.810
[mysterious music]

59
00:02:44.890 --> 00:02:45.770
What is he?

60
00:02:45.770 --> 00:02:47.810
Bullets just bounced right off him!

61
00:02:47.810 --> 00:02:50.940
Straw Hat's no ordinary
human like the rest of us.

62
00:02:50.940 --> 00:02:54.570
He must have eaten one of those devil fruits
that we've heard all those rumors about.

63
00:02:54.570 --> 00:02:55.570
Devil fruit?

64
00:02:55.570 --> 00:02:57.280
The hidden treasure of the sea.

65
00:02:57.280 --> 00:02:58.530
[KOBY]
Come on! Hurry!

66
00:02:58.530 --> 00:03:01.290
[LUFFY]
They... got... these...
things... on here tight!

67
00:03:01.290 --> 00:03:02.750
Come on! Quit screwin' around!

68
00:03:02.750 --> 00:03:07.250
It doesn't matter what abilities they have,
all who oppose me are executed!

69
00:03:07.250 --> 00:03:09.710
If the guns won't work, we chop!

70
00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:12.710
[MARINES yelling]

71
00:03:13.340 --> 00:03:14.090
[KOBY yelps]

72
00:03:14.090 --> 00:03:14.800
[LUFFY]
That's funny...

73
00:03:14.800 --> 00:03:16.720
The knots got tighter
instead of looser.

74
00:03:16.720 --> 00:03:18.300
Gimme one of my damn swords now!

75
00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:20.890
[MARINES yell]

76
00:03:20.890 --> 00:03:22.600
[KOBY screams]
Luffy, look!

77
00:03:22.600 --> 00:03:23.350
[LUFFY]
Hm?

78
00:03:23.930 --> 00:03:24.600
[KOBY screams]

79
00:03:27.560 --> 00:03:31.770
[energetic music]

80
00:03:31.770 --> 00:03:33.860
Roronoa Zoro!

81
00:03:33.860 --> 00:03:34.280
[KOBY gasps]

82
00:03:34.280 --> 00:03:36.490
Wow! That's so cool!

83
00:03:38.200 --> 00:03:39.870
Make one move and you die.

84
00:03:39.870 --> 00:03:40.910
[BOTH sobbing]

85
00:03:40.910 --> 00:03:42.660
He's scary!

86
00:03:45.620 --> 00:03:49.170
[ZORO]
Today I officially become a criminal,
having fought the Marines.

87
00:03:49.170 --> 00:03:50.670
So, I'll become a pirate.

88
00:03:50.670 --> 00:03:52.420
That, I can promise you.

89
00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:54.340
But I want you to know one thing...

90
00:03:54.340 --> 00:03:58.720
While I'm with you, the only thing
I dedicate myself to is fulfilling my ambition.

91
00:03:58.720 --> 00:03:59.590
[LUFFY]
Which is...?

92
00:03:59.590 --> 00:04:02.720
To be nothing less than
the world's greatest swordsman.

93
00:04:03.350 --> 00:04:05.480
If somewhere along the way
I have to give that up,

94
00:04:05.480 --> 00:04:07.850
then I want you to
accept responsibility.

95
00:04:07.850 --> 00:04:10.610
After which you get
to apologize to me.

96
00:04:10.610 --> 00:04:12.770
The world's greatest swordsman.

97
00:04:12.770 --> 00:04:14.360
Sounds pretty good.

98
00:04:14.360 --> 00:04:18.070
The King of the Pirates wouldn't have
any less than the best on his crew.

99
00:04:18.490 --> 00:04:19.700
Big talker.

100
00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:22.700
From this point on,
no matter if I'm a criminal or not,

101
00:04:22.700 --> 00:04:25.700
I will spread the name Zoro
throughout the world!

102
00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:27.960
What're you standing
there frozen for?!

103
00:04:27.960 --> 00:04:30.250
I want you to kill
all three of them right now!

104
00:04:31.670 --> 00:04:33.250
You might wanna duck.

105
00:04:33.250 --> 00:04:36.590
[bombastic orchestral music]

106
00:04:33.250 --> 00:04:34.000
[ZORO gasps]

107
00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:36.590
Gum-Gum...

108
00:04:36.590 --> 00:04:37.470
Whip!

109
00:04:40.430 --> 00:04:41.260
Yes!

110
00:04:41.260 --> 00:04:43.140
You knocked 'em all down! [laughs]

111
00:04:43.140 --> 00:04:45.010
Wanna tell me what you are?

112
00:04:45.350 --> 00:04:47.980
I'm just a guy who ate
the Gum-Gum Fruit.

113
00:04:47.980 --> 00:04:49.690
What's the Gum-Gum Fruit?

114
00:04:49.690 --> 00:04:51.310
A rubber person?

115
00:04:51.310 --> 00:04:53.900
[MORGAN]
It looks like he does have
the devil fruit powers.

116
00:04:53.900 --> 00:04:56.030
Captain, we don't
stand a chance against them.

117
00:04:56.030 --> 00:04:57.940
Yeah, just look at them!
They're insane!

118
00:04:57.940 --> 00:05:00.110
We couldn't even take on
Zoro by himself!

119
00:05:02.740 --> 00:05:04.580
This is a direct order!

120
00:05:04.580 --> 00:05:08.250
Every Marine that just spouted weakness,
pull your gun out and shoot yourself!

121
00:05:08.250 --> 00:05:11.290
I can't do anything with weak soldiers!

122
00:05:14.040 --> 00:05:15.800
What babies.

123
00:05:15.800 --> 00:05:16.880
This'll be easy.

124
00:05:16.880 --> 00:05:18.760
[KOBY gasps]
Luffy!

125
00:05:20.630 --> 00:05:23.340
Bring those Marines
crumbling to their knees!

126
00:05:31.310 --> 00:05:33.690
[MORGAN]
Rankless, lowlife bums!

127
00:05:33.690 --> 00:05:36.770
You have no right
to defy my superiority!

128
00:05:36.770 --> 00:05:39.490
I am Marine Captain
Axe-Hand Morgan!

129
00:05:40.610 --> 00:05:42.320
And I'm Luffy.

130
00:05:42.320 --> 00:05:43.410
Nice to meetcha.

131
00:05:43.740 --> 00:05:45.200
[MORGAN yells]

132
00:05:47.660 --> 00:05:49.250
[KOBY screams]

133
00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:56.670
Look. He's been hit!

134
00:05:56.670 --> 00:05:57.710
[MORGAN groans]

135
00:05:57.710 --> 00:05:59.340
You runt...

136
00:06:01.170 --> 00:06:02.430
Now, die!

137
00:06:02.970 --> 00:06:04.470
[LUFFY]
I don't think so!

138
00:06:06.930 --> 00:06:09.390
The captain's getting
pummeled out there.

139
00:06:11.680 --> 00:06:12.890
It's embarrassing.

140
00:06:14.440 --> 00:06:16.110
Call yourself a Marine...

141
00:06:16.110 --> 00:06:19.150
but you destroyed
my friend Koby's dream!

142
00:06:19.150 --> 00:06:20.030
[MORGAN groans]

143
00:06:20.030 --> 00:06:20.990
Straw Hat!

144
00:06:20.990 --> 00:06:22.110
Stop right there!

145
00:06:22.110 --> 00:06:23.360
Look at what I got!

146
00:06:24.780 --> 00:06:26.570
[HELMEPPO]
Are you stupid or something?!

147
00:06:26.570 --> 00:06:27.620
I said stop!

148
00:06:27.620 --> 00:06:30.750
If you would pay attention to me,
I have a hostage here you might wanna look at!

149
00:06:30.750 --> 00:06:32.580
Helmeppo's crazy...

150
00:06:32.580 --> 00:06:33.620
Hey.

151
00:06:33.620 --> 00:06:34.960
[LUFFY]
Huh?

152
00:06:34.960 --> 00:06:38.710
If you value your squatty little friend's
life, you won't move a muscle!

153
00:06:38.710 --> 00:06:41.300
I'm serious! One move
and I'll shoot him! I swear!

154
00:06:41.300 --> 00:06:41.920
[KOBY whimpers]

155
00:06:43.470 --> 00:06:44.800
[LUFFY chuckles]

156
00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:45.760
[KOBY gasps]

157
00:06:45.760 --> 00:06:46.890
Luffy, listen!

158
00:06:46.890 --> 00:06:50.180
Don't let anything that happens to me
stop you, no matter what!

159
00:06:50.180 --> 00:06:50.850
Even if I die!

160
00:06:50.850 --> 00:06:53.270
Of course. You got it.

161
00:06:53.270 --> 00:06:55.140
You hear that, you big idiot?

162
00:06:55.140 --> 00:06:57.860
Koby is ready to die by your hand!

163
00:06:58.650 --> 00:06:59.900
[HELMEPPO]
Don't you move!

164
00:06:59.900 --> 00:07:01.570
I said don't move or I'll shoot!

165
00:07:01.570 --> 00:07:02.610
I swear it!

166
00:07:02.610 --> 00:07:03.490
[energetic music]

167
00:07:03.490 --> 00:07:04.700
Luffy!

168
00:07:04.700 --> 00:07:06.110
[LUFFY] Gum Gum...
[KOBY] Behind you!

169
00:07:06.110 --> 00:07:07.620
[MORGAN]
Time's up!

170
00:07:07.620 --> 00:07:11.040
For I am fearless Marine Captain
Axe-Hand Morgan!

171
00:07:12.330 --> 00:07:14.290
Daddy, hurry up and kill him already!

172
00:07:13.700 --> 00:07:15.540
[LUFFY]
Pistol!

173
00:07:15.540 --> 00:07:17.420
[HELMEPPO screams]

174
00:07:19.960 --> 00:07:21.380
Nice one.

175
00:07:21.800 --> 00:07:25.380
[MORGAN groaning]

176
00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:31.350
[LUFFY]
Thank you.

177
00:07:31.850 --> 00:07:34.350
I'm just doing my job, Captain.

178
00:07:35.020 --> 00:07:37.980
[whimsical orchestral music]

179
00:07:35.520 --> 00:07:36.810
[LUFFY chuckles]

180
00:07:39.810 --> 00:07:41.770
[KOBY whimpers, sighs]

181
00:07:41.770 --> 00:07:43.480
[MARINE A]
Captain Morgan's been beaten.

182
00:07:43.480 --> 00:07:44.690
[MARINE B]
Unbelievable!

183
00:07:44.690 --> 00:07:46.360
[MARINE C]
Those guys are unreal!

184
00:07:47.530 --> 00:07:51.580
If there's anyone else who wants to
step forward to fight us, then do it now.

185
00:07:51.580 --> 00:07:53.540
[MARINES gasping, murmuring]

186
00:07:54.370 --> 00:07:55.620
[MARINES cheering]

187
00:07:55.620 --> 00:07:57.080
[MARINE D]
We're free!

188
00:07:57.080 --> 00:07:59.460
[MARINE E]
Finally! Morgan's reign is over!

189
00:07:59.460 --> 00:08:00.500
[MARINE F]
It's really happening!

190
00:08:00.500 --> 00:08:02.670
[MARINE G]
Such a glorious day!

191
00:08:02.670 --> 00:08:03.670
That's weird...

192
00:08:03.670 --> 00:08:06.920
Looks like they're all happy
that their captain was beaten.

193
00:08:06.920 --> 00:08:10.140
They must've been afraid of him
for a long time before we showed up.

194
00:08:10.510 --> 00:08:13.260
[ZORO groaning]

195
00:08:13.260 --> 00:08:14.430
[LUFFY, KOBY gasp]

196
00:08:14.430 --> 00:08:17.270
[KOBY]
Zoro! Are you okay?! What's wrong?!

197
00:08:17.850 --> 00:08:19.100
I'm just...

198
00:08:19.100 --> 00:08:20.400
hungry.

199
00:08:20.810 --> 00:08:23.980
[TOWNSPEOPLE chattering]

200
00:08:23.190 --> 00:08:27.360
[whimsical music]

201
00:08:23.980 --> 00:08:26.610
[ZORO]
Whew! I am stuffed!

202
00:08:26.610 --> 00:08:27.360
[sighs]

203
00:08:27.360 --> 00:08:29.110
Having not eaten for three weeks,

204
00:08:29.110 --> 00:08:32.320
I was ready to gnaw
through my boot straps.

205
00:08:31.700 --> 00:08:34.830
[GROUP laughing]

206
00:08:36.080 --> 00:08:37.710
I can't believe you're finished.

207
00:08:37.710 --> 00:08:38.540
Lightweight.

208
00:08:39.040 --> 00:08:42.250
How the hell can you have a bigger appetite
than a guy who hasn't eaten in weeks?

209
00:08:42.250 --> 00:08:44.840
[LUFFY]
It just tastes too good,
I guess. Right, Koby?

210
00:08:44.840 --> 00:08:46.130
Uh, yeah, It's great.

211
00:08:46.130 --> 00:08:47.760
Thanks for fixing it for us.

212
00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:49.050
My pleasure.

213
00:08:49.050 --> 00:08:51.220
After all, you guys did save the town.

214
00:08:51.220 --> 00:08:54.010
You're the most amazing
man I've ever met!

215
00:08:54.010 --> 00:08:55.510
Yeah, I am, I know.

216
00:08:55.510 --> 00:09:00.020
I'll be more amazing when I'm King of
the Pirates, and I have the One Piece.

217
00:09:00.020 --> 00:09:02.100
Oh, and the best crew on the seas.

218
00:09:02.520 --> 00:09:03.440
Luffy?

219
00:09:03.440 --> 00:09:06.690
Where are you and your crew
planning on traveling when you leave here?

220
00:09:06.690 --> 00:09:08.070
You mean it's not obvious?

221
00:09:08.070 --> 00:09:10.360
We're headed straight
for the Grand Line.

222
00:09:11.530 --> 00:09:13.280
No! Have you completely
lost your mind?!

223
00:09:13.280 --> 00:09:14.410
You have two crew members!

224
00:09:14.410 --> 00:09:16.580
There's no way you're equipped
to handle the Grand Line, Luffy!

225
00:09:16.580 --> 00:09:20.290
I've heard about it, but I never
knew it was such an awful place.

226
00:09:20.290 --> 00:09:22.290
It's worse than you think!

227
00:09:22.290 --> 00:09:25.040
You know that this world
has two oceans, I'm sure.

228
00:09:25.040 --> 00:09:28.420
There is an enormous landmass
that cuts across both of them.

229
00:09:28.420 --> 00:09:30.340
This is called the Red Line.

230
00:09:30.930 --> 00:09:34.600
Legend tells of a town that sits
dead center on the Red Line.

231
00:09:34.600 --> 00:09:38.220
The Grand Line is said to cut
through this town at a right angle

232
00:09:38.220 --> 00:09:41.390
and stretch all the way around the rest of the world.

233
00:09:42.230 --> 00:09:46.610
The story goes on to say that
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates,

234
00:09:46.610 --> 00:09:49.920
had once obtained everything
this world had to offer.

235
00:09:49.920 --> 00:09:55.450
Before he died, he said that he left
the great One Piece treasure at this location.

236
00:09:55.450 --> 00:09:59.410
Ever since, pirates have set sail
for the Grand Line.

237
00:09:59.410 --> 00:10:02.790
Today, the place
is nothing but a battlefield,

238
00:10:02.790 --> 00:10:06.130
and some even call it
the pirate graveyard.

239
00:10:08.670 --> 00:10:11.420
[RIRIKA]
I heard stories about it
from people passing through.

240
00:10:11.420 --> 00:10:14.180
The customers say that no one
who has ever entered the Grand Line

241
00:10:14.180 --> 00:10:15.890
comes out of that place alive.

242
00:10:15.890 --> 00:10:17.350
Which is really too bad

243
00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:21.100
'cause that's where the One Piece is said to be,
and that's exactly where we're going.

244
00:10:21.600 --> 00:10:23.060
I guess we have to live with it.

245
00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:25.100
No! You can't agree!

246
00:10:25.100 --> 00:10:26.940
[ZORO]
What do you care?
You're not going with us, are you?

247
00:10:26.940 --> 00:10:28.650
No... But I still worry...

248
00:10:28.650 --> 00:10:31.740
Is it so wrong to care
about the two of you?

249
00:10:31.740 --> 00:10:34.490
Luffy and I haven't known
each other for years or anything,

250
00:10:34.490 --> 00:10:36.490
but I'd still consider him a friend.

251
00:10:36.490 --> 00:10:37.450
Wouldn't you say?

252
00:10:37.450 --> 00:10:38.450
Of course!

253
00:10:38.450 --> 00:10:41.410
We may have to part ways
but we'll always be friends.

254
00:10:45.370 --> 00:10:49.380
[KOBY]
When I was a just little kid,
I never had any friends,

255
00:10:49.380 --> 00:10:52.840
much less anyone who would bother
fighting on my behalf.

256
00:10:52.840 --> 00:10:56.930
[soft music]
So I always tried my hardest
never to fight for anything.

257
00:10:58.800 --> 00:11:01.680
But the two of you have taught me a
lesson I could never learn on my own:

258
00:11:01.680 --> 00:11:03.810
How to live for what I believe in!

259
00:11:03.810 --> 00:11:07.060
So I've decided to make
my one childhood dream a reality,

260
00:11:07.060 --> 00:11:09.360
and I'm going to join the Marines!

261
00:11:09.360 --> 00:11:12.610
[ZORO]
Then don't you think you should be
a little more concerned with your situation?

262
00:11:13.190 --> 00:11:13.820
[KOBY gasps]

263
00:11:14.490 --> 00:11:17.240
I mean, you did spend two years
on Alvida's pirate ship,

264
00:11:17.240 --> 00:11:19.530
even if you were nothing
but her cabin boy.

265
00:11:21.700 --> 00:11:24.500
The Marines' information
gathering is top-notch.

266
00:11:24.500 --> 00:11:27.290
They'll find out about your time
with Alvida, and you'll never join.

267
00:11:27.790 --> 00:11:29.590
I... never thought of that...

268
00:11:30.960 --> 00:11:32.000
[LIEUTENANT]
Hey! You there.

269
00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:33.260
[KOBY, RIKA gasp]

270
00:11:36.260 --> 00:11:37.930
We heard that you fellas
are actually pirates.

271
00:11:37.930 --> 00:11:39.300
Is this rumor true?

272
00:11:39.300 --> 00:11:41.810
Right, and I just added
the first member to my crew.

273
00:11:41.810 --> 00:11:44.560
So pretty much the whole thing
just became official.

274
00:11:44.560 --> 00:11:46.940
We appreciate everything
you did to save our town

275
00:11:46.940 --> 00:11:50.360
from that horrible tyrant
who terrorized us all for so long.

276
00:11:50.360 --> 00:11:52.320
However, now that
we know that you're pirates,

277
00:11:52.320 --> 00:11:56.070
we cannot sit idly by and watch
you go about your business.

278
00:11:56.070 --> 00:11:59.700
Therefore, you and your crew
will need to leave this town immediately.

279
00:11:59.700 --> 00:12:03.580
[menacing music]

280
00:11:59.700 --> 00:12:01.330
But out of respect
for what you've done,

281
00:12:01.330 --> 00:12:03.580
we will not report
you to headquarters.

282
00:12:03.580 --> 00:12:04.540
Are you crazy?

283
00:12:04.540 --> 00:12:06.500
How do you find
the nerve to talk like that?!

284
00:12:06.500 --> 00:12:08.210
[MAN]
Before these pirates came along,

285
00:12:08.210 --> 00:12:10.330
you guys were as scared
of Morgan as we were.

286
00:12:10.330 --> 00:12:12.710
[WOMAN]
Without them,
we'd still be under his reign.

287
00:12:12.710 --> 00:12:14.000
We owe them our lives!

288
00:12:14.000 --> 00:12:17.970
[TOWNSPEOPLE grumbling]

289
00:12:17.970 --> 00:12:18.590
[LUFFY chuckles]

290
00:12:18.590 --> 00:12:20.590
Well, time to go!

291
00:12:20.590 --> 00:12:22.100
Thanks for all of the food, lady.

292
00:12:22.100 --> 00:12:25.020
Hey, wait a second.
You're leaving already?

293
00:12:25.020 --> 00:12:26.230
Yeah.

294
00:12:33.150 --> 00:12:35.570
[LIEUTENANT]
Aren't you part of the crew, as well?

295
00:12:35.570 --> 00:12:39.610
[KOBY gasps]
Uh, well, I... uh... I...

296
00:12:43.330 --> 00:12:44.160
[LIEUTENANT]
Hold it!

297
00:12:44.160 --> 00:12:46.200
Is he with you or what?

298
00:12:46.950 --> 00:12:50.170
What I can tell you is what
he's been busy doing up to this point.

299
00:12:51.000 --> 00:12:52.920
[KOBY]
Luffy! You wouldn't!

300
00:12:53.250 --> 00:12:56.380
Yeah, there was this
fantastically fat pirate lady.

301
00:12:56.380 --> 00:12:58.130
I think her name was Alvida.

302
00:12:58.130 --> 00:12:59.300
Luffy...

303
00:13:00.130 --> 00:13:02.720
[KOBY]
If they find out I ran
with a pirate crew,

304
00:13:02.720 --> 00:13:04.850
I'll never join the Marines.

305
00:13:05.390 --> 00:13:07.890
She carried around
this huge iron club and, boy,

306
00:13:07.890 --> 00:13:10.850
she was the nastiest looking
woman I've ever seen.

307
00:13:10.850 --> 00:13:14.440
For two years, this wimpy kid
was her own private cabin boy.

308
00:13:14.770 --> 00:13:15.900
[KOBY]
Please stop!

309
00:13:15.900 --> 00:13:17.610
You can't do this!

310
00:13:17.610 --> 00:13:18.900
Luffy, no!

311
00:13:19.740 --> 00:13:20.860
[KOBY yells]

312
00:13:20.860 --> 00:13:21.860
[BOTH gasp]

313
00:13:21.860 --> 00:13:22.950
[MARINES gasp]

314
00:13:23.950 --> 00:13:24.660
[ZORO]
Hm.

315
00:13:25.160 --> 00:13:26.620
[KOBY whimpers, gasps]

316
00:13:26.620 --> 00:13:28.160
[LUFFY chuckles]

317
00:13:28.160 --> 00:13:29.790
Now that was a dumb move!

318
00:13:30.120 --> 00:13:35.250
[KOBY, LUFFY grunting]

319
00:13:32.290 --> 00:13:33.420
[LUFFY] Bastard!

320
00:13:35.250 --> 00:13:36.630
Get out of here now!

321
00:13:36.630 --> 00:13:40.470
We can't have you pirates ripping up this town
any more than you already have, you hear me?!

322
00:13:40.470 --> 00:13:41.430
[ZORO]
Enough.

323
00:13:41.800 --> 00:13:42.930
You made your point.

324
00:13:42.930 --> 00:13:44.600
Now let him fall to the ground.

325
00:13:45.930 --> 00:13:49.100
[KOBY panting]

326
00:13:49.770 --> 00:13:52.140
It's obvious you're not
crewmates, so stop badgering

327
00:13:52.140 --> 00:13:55.020
the poor kid and take your leave
of our town this instant!

328
00:13:55.360 --> 00:13:56.070
[LUFFY]
Heh.

329
00:13:57.480 --> 00:13:58.280
[KOBY]
Huh?

330
00:14:00.570 --> 00:14:03.030
That was on purpose?

331
00:14:03.820 --> 00:14:06.280
Luffy did that just to help me out...

332
00:14:10.080 --> 00:14:15.290
He worked me up and got me so mad that
I'd hit him and look like I wasn't on his side.

333
00:14:17.540 --> 00:14:19.760
Even at the very end
of our journey together,

334
00:14:19.760 --> 00:14:22.630
I wound up continuing to rely on him.

335
00:14:22.630 --> 00:14:25.180
I couldn't do anything for myself.

336
00:14:25.890 --> 00:14:28.850
Nothing's changed for me at all.

337
00:14:30.850 --> 00:14:33.560
[KOBY]
I am such an idiot!

338
00:14:34.020 --> 00:14:34.560
Sir!

339
00:14:34.560 --> 00:14:35.270
[LIEUTENANT]
Hm?

340
00:14:35.980 --> 00:14:36.560
Please, sir!

341
00:14:36.560 --> 00:14:38.690
Please, you have to
let me join the Marines!

342
00:14:38.690 --> 00:14:42.070
I'll clean and scrub and do
any chores that you'd like me to!

343
00:14:42.070 --> 00:14:44.490
I'll do anything to become a Marine!

344
00:14:47.490 --> 00:14:48.660
Lieutenant.

345
00:14:48.660 --> 00:14:50.450
I can't say I fully trust this kid.

346
00:14:51.200 --> 00:14:53.750
I wouldn't be against the idea
if there weren't clear cases

347
00:14:53.750 --> 00:14:57.080
of certain Marines
actually being pirate spies.

348
00:14:57.580 --> 00:15:00.090
I say, we should conduct
a background check first.

349
00:15:00.550 --> 00:15:04.090
No matter what you say, I am
a man who will become a Marine!

350
00:15:07.300 --> 00:15:08.180
[LIETUTENANT]
Hmm...

351
00:15:10.510 --> 00:15:12.560
I can't tell you
how many of our comrades

352
00:15:12.560 --> 00:15:15.310
have been killed
by pirates over the years.

353
00:15:15.310 --> 00:15:17.310
This is a big step you're taking.

354
00:15:17.310 --> 00:15:17.900
So...

355
00:15:17.900 --> 00:15:20.070
[LIEUTENANT]
Permission to join granted.

356
00:15:21.900 --> 00:15:23.150
Sir!

357
00:15:24.820 --> 00:15:26.820
[ZORO]
That was a thin act
you put on back there.

358
00:15:26.820 --> 00:15:28.530
I wouldn't be surprised
if they see right through it.

359
00:15:28.530 --> 00:15:32.330
[LUFFY laughs]
Koby should be able to handle the
rest on his own. I have faith in him.

360
00:15:32.330 --> 00:15:34.160
[ZORO]
It is a fitting way to leave this place,

361
00:15:34.160 --> 00:15:36.870
unable to turn back 'cause
everyone here hates us now.

362
00:15:36.870 --> 00:15:38.630
Very pirate-like.

363
00:15:38.960 --> 00:15:39.540
[laughs]

364
00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:41.300
Yeah. It sure is.

365
00:15:41.300 --> 00:15:41.880
[KOBY]
Luffy!

366
00:15:41.880 --> 00:15:42.550
[LUFFY]
Huh?

367
00:15:44.550 --> 00:15:46.300
I can never thank you enough!

368
00:15:46.300 --> 00:15:48.890
You've done more for me
than anyone ever has!

369
00:15:49.220 --> 00:15:51.930
[ZORO]
I've never heard of a Marine
thanking a pirate before.

370
00:15:51.930 --> 00:15:53.520
That's one for the history books.

371
00:15:53.520 --> 00:15:54.890
[LUFFY chuckling]

372
00:15:55.850 --> 00:15:57.980
[LUFFY]
We'll meet again, Koby!

373
00:15:57.980 --> 00:15:58.850
Someday!

374
00:15:58.850 --> 00:16:00.110
Bye, Luffy.

375
00:16:00.110 --> 00:16:02.320
Hope to see you again someday!

376
00:16:02.320 --> 00:16:03.320
All hands...

377
00:16:03.320 --> 00:16:05.030
salute!

378
00:16:05.610 --> 00:16:06.280
[KOBY gasps]

379
00:16:07.990 --> 00:16:10.030
See ya!

380
00:16:11.780 --> 00:16:13.910
[LIEUTENANT]
That's a good friend you have there.

381
00:16:15.870 --> 00:16:19.000
[grandiose orchestral music]

382
00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:19.960
Yeah!

383
00:16:19.960 --> 00:16:20.830
[LIEUTENANT]
Men!

384
00:16:20.830 --> 00:16:24.460
Seeing as our current salute
is in violation of Marine law,

385
00:16:24.460 --> 00:16:27.420
we will all go without food
for three days!

386
00:16:27.420 --> 00:16:29.800
Do we all understand this?!

387
00:16:29.800 --> 00:16:30.970
[MARINES, KOBY]
Yes, sir!

388
00:16:33.810 --> 00:16:36.060
[LUFFY]
Now! Let's go!

389
00:16:36.060 --> 00:16:38.560
It's time for us to set our heading...

390
00:16:38.560 --> 00:16:41.150
for the Grand Line!

391
00:16:52.660 --> 00:16:59.520
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

392
00:16:59.720 --> 00:17:06.540
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

393
00:17:06.790 --> 00:17:13.640
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

394
00:17:13.760 --> 00:17:20.900
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

395
00:17:23.600 --> 00:17:26.280
Look where I am

396
00:17:28.510 --> 00:17:34.690
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

397
00:17:35.030 --> 00:17:41.960
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

398
00:17:42.120 --> 00:17:49.040
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

399
00:17:49.170 --> 00:17:56.170
Take me to the place where memories remain

400
00:17:56.270 --> 00:18:02.040
Please don't ever let them fade
